# coverage.baseline — Harmonik per-package coverage baseline (hk-pvcs.5)
#
# FORMAT: one entry per line
#   <fully-qualified-package-path> <coverage-pct>
#
# Example (once packages land):
#   github.com/gregberns/harmonik/internal/core/scheduler 97.3
#   github.com/gregberns/harmonik/internal/eventbus       91.5
#
# POLICY (quality-checks.md §Agent-enforceability):
#   This is a "protected rule file". Any commit that edits this file MUST:
#   1. Cite a kerf codename in the commit body explaining why the baseline changed.
#   2. Be a single-concern commit (baseline bump OR code change, not both).
#   3. Trigger the `rule-change` CI surface (watches this path).
#   Agents MUST bump the baseline when coverage genuinely improves (ratchet up);
#   lowering an entry or deleting it is treated as a rule relaxation and requires
#   the same single-concern commit protocol.
#
# CURRENT STATE: initial population per hk-41cns (2026-05-20). Coverage profile
# generated via `go test -coverprofile=/tmp/cover.out -covermode=atomic ./internal/...`.
# Packages without statements (internal/specaudit, internal/t5probe, internal/scenario,
# internal/release) and internal/testhelpers (excluded per coverage-gate.sh) are
# omitted. Per-package floors and regression gate (<0.3pp drop) now active.
